Installing NFS Server 

Step 1
Command to first we have to do install nfs-kernel-server :- sudo apt-get -y install nfs-kernel-server

Step 2 
Command to Then create a new directory and file in this  :- mkdir  dir_name
then open shell script and add a file in it , Command :- vi abc.txt

Step 3  
Command to  Open /etc/exports :- sudo vi /etc/exports

Step 4  
Command to and we have to add line at the end of file :- home/kali/dir_name 127.0.0.1(rw)

Step 5  
Command to use below commnand to will create a table and see records :- sudo export -ra

Step 6  
Command to install nfs-common is present or than we have to use this cammand , if not found :- sudo apt-get -y install nfs-common

Step 7  
Command to mount the file you want to transfer in other directory :- sudo mount -t nfs 127.0.0.1:[dir_name] [dir_name2]
    
    
